                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The big carnival bear isn't well trained yet, though it might occasionally respond to commands. Whatever its current attitude, use the following degrees of success instead of the usual check results for attempts to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Command an Animal] against the big carnival bear.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The bear does as commanded on its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The bear acts normally (as determined by the GM) on its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The bear attacks the creature attempting to command it on its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The bear attacks the creature attempting to command it on its next turn, and becomes immune to Command an Animal for 1 minute.</p>"
